The Keiser Report  No. 196
= Max Keiser and Stacy Herbert =
Thursday, 13 October 2011


[sebaygo1]


This time Max and Stacy talk about the Sarkozy-Merkel dog and pony show announcing the plan without a plan and about when an asset isn't really an asset. 

In the second half of the show, Max Keiser interviews Ellen Brown, author of Web of Debt, about the German Landesbanks and a Swiss community currency.        



The .mp3 in the torrent is audio extracted from the Russia Today video. You can watch the video online at:

 that counters the monotone of mainstream corporate media.
